    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Methylcarboxypyrrolidonyl Ethylenediamine/Methyl Acrylate Dendrimer is the multibranched polymer formed by reacting 1,4-butanediamine with methyl acrylate followed by reaction with Ethylenediamine. The sequential reaction of methyl acrylate and Ethylenediamine is repeated to obtain a four-generation dendrimer. The dendrimer is capped by reacting it with Dimethyl Itaconate."
    ],
